345
00:20:53,461 --> 00:20:56,839
I close my eyes slowly

346
00:20:58,091 --> 00:20:59,384
and open them quickly.

347
00:21:01,427 --> 00:21:05,223
Then, suddenly, I whisper.

348
00:21:07,350 --> 00:21:08,267
What's that?

349
00:21:08,351 --> 00:21:13,147
We get really close.

350
00:21:20,446 --> 00:21:22,281
So that was your seduction skills?

351
00:21:22,907 --> 00:21:23,783
Yes.

352
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,952
-Seduction?
-Yes.

353
00:21:30,039 --> 00:21:32,208
Seduction? For real?

354
00:21:33,710 --> 00:21:35,795
Come on.

355
00:21:35,878 --> 00:21:38,464
This is supposed to work.

356
00:21:38,548 --> 00:21:40,133
Unbelievable.

357
00:21:40,216 --> 00:21:43,886
You need to be open-minded
for this to work.

358
00:21:43,970 --> 00:21:46,764
If you're that close-minded,
how can this work?

359
00:21:46,848 --> 00:21:49,434
A magic show works
when the audience just watches.

360
00:21:49,517 --> 00:21:52,979
If you doubt every trick,
even David Copperfield can't make it work.

361
00:21:53,062 --> 00:21:56,190
No, it's not that kind of a problem.

362
00:21:57,066 --> 00:22:00,319
With that,
no matter how open-minded a guy is,

363
00:22:00,403 --> 00:22:02,697
I don't think you can
get the results you desire.

364
00:22:03,573 --> 00:22:05,074
Was it that bad?

365
00:22:05,158 --> 00:22:06,909
You're not just saying that?

366
00:22:06,993 --> 00:22:09,120
I dare myself to evaluate.

367
00:22:09,662 --> 00:22:11,622
It was obnoxiously cheesy,

368
00:22:11,706 --> 00:22:13,833
let alone attractive.

369
00:22:13,916 --> 00:22:16,294
The acting was over the top and insincere.

370
00:22:16,377 --> 00:22:22,008
It even made me wonder
how I need to react to this.

371
00:22:22,925 --> 00:22:25,720
It was a pretty unpleasant performance.

372
00:22:28,723 --> 00:22:30,558
Still, I had some good laughs.

373
00:22:30,892 --> 00:22:33,686
Maybe not now,
but you'll think about me before bed.

374
00:22:33,770 --> 00:22:35,146
Is that a curse?

375
00:22:35,229 --> 00:22:36,397
A curse?

376
00:22:36,481 --> 00:22:38,691
Anyways, you failed to prove it.

377
00:22:41,944 --> 00:22:42,945
Ms. Yeon.

378
00:22:43,321 --> 00:22:47,408
Now is the time to trust your intuition.

379
00:22:48,826 --> 00:22:51,662
If you can't make up for it
with the next plan,

380
00:22:51,746 --> 00:22:55,666
we might have to reconsider
our publishing plan for your book.

381
00:22:55,750 --> 00:22:58,836
I got an idea about the next plan.

382
00:23:02,090 --> 00:23:03,299
Plan 1.

383
00:23:03,716 --> 00:23:05,426
I'll break up with him.

384
00:23:06,427 --> 00:23:09,138
Did you forget you'd broken up
with him already?

385
00:23:10,264 --> 00:23:12,683
I really don't like the ending.

386
00:23:12,767 --> 00:23:15,103
I'll rewrite the ending of this story.

387
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:20,525
Listen.

388
00:23:20,608 --> 00:23:23,528
Humans have a tendency to forget.

389
00:23:23,611 --> 00:23:26,239
According to
the Ebbinghaus Forgetting Curve,

390
00:23:26,322 --> 00:23:29,575
more than 50% of new information
is forgotten within the first hour,

391
00:23:29,659 --> 00:23:33,621
70% within 24 hours,
and 80% within a month.

392
00:23:34,413 --> 00:23:36,165
Then what do we have left?

393
00:23:36,582 --> 00:23:38,918
Human brains have
a limited memory capacity.

394
00:23:39,001 --> 00:23:42,130
Our brain remembers
only the first and last parts.

395
00:23:42,213 --> 00:23:44,257
That's why, in a romantic relationship,

396
00:23:44,340 --> 00:23:46,801
the first and last impressions
are crucial.

397
00:23:47,510 --> 00:23:52,098
While the first impression defines
the general image of a person,

398
00:23:52,181 --> 00:23:56,644
the last impression forms
a lasting image you'll remember.

399
00:23:57,311 --> 00:23:58,354
Got it?

400
00:23:58,437 --> 00:24:00,815
Yes, I understand.

401
00:24:01,357 --> 00:24:05,528
The last impression he has of me is...

402
00:24:07,989 --> 00:24:11,200
a woman wearing pajamas
and slippers with disheveled hair.

403
00:24:11,284 --> 00:24:12,535
Are you drunk?

404
00:24:12,618 --> 00:24:14,495
I was drunk, my face was puffy,

405
00:24:15,496 --> 00:24:18,875
I wailed and was clingy.

406
00:24:20,501 --> 00:24:21,335
I remember that.

407
00:24:22,420 --> 00:24:24,922
With that horrible last impression,

408
00:24:25,006 --> 00:24:28,301
I won't last in his memories,
let alone see him again.

409
00:24:28,384 --> 00:24:32,180
That's why I'm going to
break up with him again.

410
00:24:32,847 --> 00:24:37,435
You'll break up again
and change the last impression?

411
00:24:38,477 --> 00:24:39,729
How does that sound?

412
00:24:40,354 --> 00:24:42,565
Would it be enough to make up for it?

413
00:24:45,860 --> 00:24:49,197
You make a valid point.
It's interesting as well.

414
00:24:50,198 --> 00:24:51,407
Right?

415
00:24:57,246 --> 00:24:59,123
Anyways, the problem is

416
00:24:59,207 --> 00:25:03,127
I have to see him again
in order to break up again.

417
00:25:03,211 --> 00:25:04,503
Why is that a problem?

418
00:25:05,421 --> 00:25:07,548
It has to be a coincidence.

419
00:25:08,257 --> 00:25:11,219
If I tell him that I want to see him,

420
00:25:11,594 --> 00:25:14,138
he'd bring his lawyer.

421
00:25:14,222 --> 00:25:16,974
If I go to his house,
he might call the police.

422
00:25:18,559 --> 00:25:20,186
That's possible.

423
00:25:21,145 --> 00:25:25,566
Then how can you see him
coincidentally on purpose?

424
00:25:26,734 --> 00:25:29,904
That's why we came here.

425
00:25:36,744 --> 00:25:38,955
It's been a while.

426
00:25:39,038 --> 00:25:40,081
How are you?

427
00:25:40,164 --> 00:25:42,333
It's been so long.

428
00:25:42,416 --> 00:25:45,503
I was thinking that
it was about time you two come back...

429
00:25:49,090 --> 00:25:51,342
-Sit anywhere you want, please.
-Okay.

430
00:26:03,312 --> 00:26:05,898
This is his soul food.

431
00:26:06,774 --> 00:26:09,026
He comes here at least once a week.

432
00:26:09,110 --> 00:26:12,780
He may forget me,
but he can't forget these noodles.

433
00:26:12,863 --> 00:26:14,657
He will definitely come back.

434
00:26:15,032 --> 00:26:18,703
This is the perfect place
to coincidentally run into him on purpose.

435
00:26:21,872 --> 00:26:23,666
What was your last impression like?

436
00:26:26,836 --> 00:26:28,587
Why are you being so nosy?

437
00:26:28,671 --> 00:26:31,716
We're in the same boat,
let's help each other out.

438
00:26:32,091 --> 00:26:33,175
Who knows?

439
00:26:33,259 --> 00:26:36,887
Maybe your last impression was worse,
and I'd feel better after hearing it.

440
00:26:38,931 --> 00:26:41,100
I don't think it'd make you feel better.

441
00:26:42,643 --> 00:26:44,562
Because I lost quite gracefully.

442
00:26:44,645 --> 00:26:47,565
When she wanted to break up,
I accepted it without resistance.

443
00:26:48,858 --> 00:26:51,027
She was taking a taxi,

444
00:26:51,652 --> 00:26:53,654
I ran and gave her some cold medicine,

445
00:26:54,155 --> 00:26:56,574
because she was sniffling due to a cold.

446
00:26:57,158 --> 00:27:00,870
You left the worst last impression
on her as well.

447
00:27:01,329 --> 00:27:04,248
You made it harder for her
to hate you when splitting up.

448
00:27:04,332 --> 00:27:06,292
Why did you have to be so sweet?

449
00:27:11,964 --> 00:27:13,883
I want to lose gracefully.

450
00:27:14,884 --> 00:27:17,595
Even if the other player played dirty,

451
00:27:17,678 --> 00:27:20,139
I want to graciously protect my dignity

452
00:27:21,807 --> 00:27:24,352
and accept the results.

453
00:27:30,024 --> 00:27:31,359
Maybe not now,

454
00:27:32,902 --> 00:27:35,696
but you'll think about me before bed.

455
00:27:38,324 --> 00:27:39,992
Not in the slightest.

456
00:27:40,534 --> 00:27:42,828
I'm so falling asleep.

457
00:27:44,872 --> 00:27:47,249
You smell nice. What cologne do you use?

458
00:27:49,001 --> 00:27:50,544
My cologne smells nice?

459
00:27:51,962 --> 00:27:55,591
Cologne is supposed to smell nice.

460
00:27:55,674 --> 00:27:57,093
Then...

461
00:27:57,968 --> 00:27:59,512
Why's she stroking her hair?

462
00:27:59,595 --> 00:28:01,555
