we'd be together. Didn't you?

809
00:50:47,420 --> 00:50:48,379
I did.

810
00:50:50,548 --> 00:50:52,925
Let's go have pork cutlet. I'm hungry.

811
00:50:53,634 --> 00:50:54,594
Okay.

812
00:50:59,682 --> 00:51:00,850
By the way,

813
00:51:02,435 --> 00:51:04,020
can I hold your hand?

814
00:51:06,272 --> 00:51:08,274
I just took a chance. Never mind.

815
00:51:13,112 --> 00:51:14,906
Happy now? Let's go.

816
00:51:16,282 --> 00:51:17,283
Okay.

817
00:51:39,138 --> 00:51:40,515
Sunday at 2:00 p.m.

818
00:51:40,598 --> 00:51:42,892
I'll call you.
I'll give you a wake-up call.

819
00:51:45,520 --> 00:51:46,604
Sunday at 2:00 p.m.

820
00:51:46,687 --> 00:51:48,940
Sunday at 2:00 p.m.
at the naengmyeon place.

821
00:51:53,277 --> 00:51:55,947
Please do me a favor.
Okay? You'll come, right?

822
00:51:56,030 --> 00:51:56,948
It's 2:00 p.m.

823
00:51:57,448 --> 00:51:59,826
See you at 2:00 p.m. Sunday at 2:00 p.m.

824
00:52:02,119 --> 00:52:03,496
It's 2:00 p.m.

825
00:52:03,579 --> 00:52:07,500
Jeez, okay. I got it.

826
00:52:48,457 --> 00:52:49,792
What was that?

827
00:52:53,254 --> 00:52:55,548
So cold-blooded. Is he really not coming?

828
00:52:57,717 --> 00:53:00,428
Is he ever coming today?

829
00:53:01,470 --> 00:53:03,556
-Probably.
-"Probably"?

830
00:53:04,640 --> 00:53:05,850
You say that now?

831
00:53:05,933 --> 00:53:07,143
Almost certainly.

832
00:53:08,185 --> 00:53:12,064
Based on the extensive data
accumulated for years and my gut feeling,

833
00:53:12,148 --> 00:53:14,483
it's highly likely that he'll come today.

834
00:53:15,318 --> 00:53:17,403
Every Sunday, he goes to church,

835
00:53:17,486 --> 00:53:20,865
hits the gym and sauna,
and has naengmyeon here,

836
00:53:20,948 --> 00:53:23,659
to wrap up the week on a high note.

837
00:53:24,410 --> 00:53:27,955
So, you mean, if he doesn't show up today,

838
00:53:28,039 --> 00:53:30,791
we'd have to do this every Sunday?

839
00:53:31,959 --> 00:53:33,544
Why do you ask the obvious?

840
00:53:35,004 --> 00:53:37,673
Do you think I have no life?

841
00:53:38,341 --> 00:53:39,175
Come on.

842
00:53:39,258 --> 00:53:41,469
I need to rest on the weekends.

843
00:53:43,804 --> 00:53:44,764
Is he here?

844
00:53:44,847 --> 00:53:46,057
I think he's here.

845
00:53:49,977 --> 00:53:50,978
Be careful.

846
00:54:02,073 --> 00:54:03,449
How do I look?

847
00:54:04,450 --> 00:54:07,370
-Do I look okay now?
-Yes, you do.

848
00:54:07,453 --> 00:54:08,663
-Really?
-Yes.

849
00:54:11,290 --> 00:54:12,124
I'll be back.

850
00:54:12,750 --> 00:54:13,668
Good luck.

851
00:54:33,771 --> 00:54:34,772
Thank you.

852
00:54:39,110 --> 00:54:40,194
Hi.

853
00:54:45,449 --> 00:54:46,575
Can we talk?

854
00:54:48,119 --> 00:54:48,953
Okay.

855
00:54:56,460 --> 00:54:57,545
You look well.

856
00:55:00,256 --> 00:55:03,384
How's everything? How's work?

857
00:55:04,552 --> 00:55:05,594
Same old.

858
00:55:09,432 --> 00:55:14,437
I actually wanted to
talk with you in person

859
00:55:15,187 --> 00:55:16,355
when I'm sober.

860
00:55:17,565 --> 00:55:21,193
I thought you might come around this time,
and here you are.

861
00:55:26,824 --> 00:55:29,243
I agree with what you said.

862
00:55:29,702 --> 00:55:31,829
I'm glad we parted ways.

863
00:55:36,083 --> 00:55:39,920
If we make each other unhappy,
it's right to go our separate ways.

864
00:55:44,300 --> 00:55:45,301
I'm sorry.

865
00:55:46,093 --> 00:55:47,136
Right.

866
00:55:47,887 --> 00:55:49,764
You should be sorry to me.

867
00:55:50,931 --> 00:55:53,392
You could've been honest with me
and broken up,

868
00:55:53,476 --> 00:55:54,935
I would have understood.

869
00:55:56,353 --> 00:55:59,190
It's not the end of the world
even if we break up.

870
00:56:01,442 --> 00:56:03,360
I'm doing well, as you can see.

871
00:56:04,779 --> 00:56:05,863
Yeah.

872
00:56:08,032 --> 00:56:09,158
You look great.

873
00:56:11,786 --> 00:56:15,831
Of course, I would have needed
some time to process it.

874
00:56:17,249 --> 00:56:21,295
You should have waited for me till then,

875
00:56:21,754 --> 00:56:24,090
considering the time we spent together.

876
00:56:27,218 --> 00:56:28,094
But,

877
00:56:29,261 --> 00:56:32,807
since we broke up because of someone else,

878
00:56:34,391 --> 00:56:36,435
I had to go through hard times.

879
00:56:39,355 --> 00:56:41,732
Right. I'm sorry about that too.

880
00:56:42,108 --> 00:56:45,444
No, I'm not asking you to say sorry.

881
00:56:46,237 --> 00:56:47,488
I just wanted to explain.

882
00:56:47,571 --> 00:56:49,907
The way I acted after our breakup...

883
00:56:53,911 --> 00:56:55,788
I was hoping you would understand me.

884
00:56:56,330 --> 00:56:58,499
Yes, I totally understand.

885
00:57:00,459 --> 00:57:01,585
That's a relief.

886
00:57:04,046 --> 00:57:07,007
At least, we got to
talk in person like this.

887
00:57:08,759 --> 00:57:12,346
Though we can't say hi
when we run into each other,

888
00:57:12,429 --> 00:57:15,307
it won't ruin our whole day
at least, right?

889
00:57:15,933 --> 00:57:16,934
Yes.

890
00:57:20,980 --> 00:57:22,773
That's all. I'm going to get going.

891
00:57:23,983 --> 00:57:24,984
Okay.

892
00:57:25,901 --> 00:57:28,529
No, finish up.

893
00:57:30,030 --> 00:57:31,949
I know you like it.

894
00:57:32,032 --> 00:57:33,993
We came practically every day in summer.

895
00:57:34,076 --> 00:57:36,245
We ate this shivering in midwinter.

896
00:57:36,328 --> 00:57:39,331
There was one time we came here all week.
Remember that?

897
00:57:43,002 --> 00:57:46,630
If you leave any, you'll regret it.
You'll think of it before bed.

898
00:57:50,092 --> 00:57:52,011
That'd be too late.

899
00:57:55,181 --> 00:57:57,016
Too late. Okay.

900
00:57:58,601 --> 00:58:01,604
Also, you can feel at ease coming here.

901
00:58:02,354 --> 00:58:04,148
I'm not coming back here.

902
00:58:06,066 --> 00:58:07,193
Take care.

903
00:58:07,985 --> 00:58:09,028
Okay.

904
00:58:47,900 --> 00:58:48,901
What?

905
00:58:49,902 --> 00:58:51,195
Why are you still here?

906
00:58:52,112 --> 00:58:53,530
Did it go well?

907
00:58:55,991 --> 00:58:57,034
Yes.

908
00:59:00,537 --> 00:59:01,997
Let me give you a ride.

909
00:59:24,895 --> 00:59:27,398
Seriously, why did you stay?

910
00:59:27,481 --> 00:59:29,733
Were you worried that I'd make a scene?

911
00:59:30,776 --> 00:59:35,906
In a movie, the female protagonist
usually gets escorted by a better man.

912
00:59:37,324 --> 00:59:39,451
Are you being serious?

913
00:59:43,664 --> 00:59:45,958
Thanks anyway.

914
00:59:47,293 --> 00:59:50,838
Walking out, my legs felt weak.

915
00:59:53,382 --> 00:59:56,552
But I did not cry.

916
01:00:00,889 --> 01:00:02,725
It's really something.

917
01:00:04,310 --> 01:00:05,811
You want my compliment?

918
01:00:07,730 --> 01:00:09,064
Well done.

919
01:00:09,815 --> 01:00:10,858
Though you lost,

920
01:00:11,817 --> 01:00:13,485
you fought the good fight.

921
01:00:16,113 --> 01:00:17,740
How do you feel after the breakup?

922
01:00:22,578 --> 01:00:25,539
She wanted to hum a tune,

923
01:00:26,123 --> 01:00:28,584
chatter away with anyone,

924
01:00:29,209 --> 01:00:33,630
and wanted to vanish into
the defenseless, bustling streets.

925
01:00:35,549 --> 01:00:37,593
You really are like Shakespeare now.

926
01:00:39,011 --> 01:00:40,721
Where are we going?

927
01:00:56,153 --> 01:00:57,196
Karaoke?

928
01:00:58,238 --> 01:01:00,074
You said you wanted to hum a tune.

929
01:01:12,711 --> 01:01:13,587
Here.

930
01:01:14,213 --> 01:01:15,756
Sing your lungs out.

931
01:01:18,926 --> 01:01:22,221
I might cry if I sing on a day like this.

932
01:01:22,638 --> 01:01:24,139
What's wrong with crying?

933
01:01:24,223 --> 01:01:26,308
It's okay to cry after breaking up.

934
01:01:26,392 --> 01:01:27,476
Don't you think?

935
01:01:27,559 --> 01:01:30,020
Okay. Here.

936
01:01:48,622 --> 01:01:51,375
He said he was leaving me

937
01:01:52,251 --> 01:01:54,670
So I told him to leave

938
01:01:55,754 --> 01:01:58,173
Thought it was a line you hear

939
01:01:58,257 --> 01:02:01,385
At least once when you love someone

940
01:02:01,468 --> 01:02:04,972
Looking at myself in the mirror

941
01:02:05,055 --> 01:02:08,892
I convinced myself he's coming back

942
01:02:08,976 --> 01:02:12,479
Have been counting so many days

943
01:02:12,563 --> 01:02:15,649
Can't even remember how many

944
01:02:17,651 --> 01:02:21,029
But I still can't see you

945
01:02:21,113 --> 01:02:24,658
Can't find where my love is

946
01:02:24,741 --> 01:02:27,870
Groping around

947
01:02:27,953 --> 01:02:31,248
Looking for your photo

948
01:02:31,331 --> 01:02:35,752
My eyes go blind

949
01:02:35,836 --> 01:02:39,256
Burst in tears

950
01:02:39,339 --> 01:02:41,133
Leaving severe bruise

951
01:02:41,216 --> 01:02:46,096
On my heart

952
01:02:47,806 --> 01:02:48,807
Told me to forg...

953
01:02:49,725 --> 01:02:51,852
-Why?
-No.

954
01:02:51,935 --> 01:02:53,187
That's not the song.

955
01:02:54,188 --> 01:02:55,105
Listen carefully.

956
01:02:56,482 --> 01:02:58,442
I HAVE NO PROBLEM

957
01:03:00,569 --> 01:03:01,862
Seriously?

958
01:03:03,906 --> 01:03:06,742
I'm on top of this world

959
01:03:06,825 --> 01:03:09,912
I want to

960
01:03:09,995 --> 01:03:13,081
Go my way

961
01:03:13,665 --> 01:03:17,127
With my people who love me
Love me!

962
01:03:17,211 --> 01:03:20,923
It was tough and lonely

963
01:03:21,006 --> 01:03:23,383
But it's just a practice

964
01:03:23,967 --> 01:03:27,012
I'm not falling down

965
01:03:27,095 --> 01:03:30,015
I have no problem!

966
01:04:15,686 --> 01:04:17,354
I think my voice is hoarse.

967
01:04:18,855 --> 01:04:19,815
How are you feeling?

968
01:04:20,274 --> 01:04:22,067
Do you feel better?

969
01:04:26,655 --> 01:04:27,823
Thanks.

970
01:04:28,907 --> 01:04:30,492
Thanks to you,

971
01:04:30,576 --> 01:04:32,244
I was able to do something.

972
01:04:34,288 --> 01:04:35,872
I think I lost gracefully.

973
01:04:37,791 --> 01:04:39,585
I feel the same.

974
01:04:40,711 --> 01:04:42,588
Ever since I met you,

975
01:04:43,380 --> 01:04:45,173
it's been so chaotic

976
01:04:46,550 --> 01:04:49,094
that tough moments passed by
before I knew it.

977
01:04:50,637 --> 01:04:53,640
I think it was kind of fun, thanks to you.

978
01:04:54,891 --> 01:04:56,768
Do you have to add "I think"?

979
01:04:58,145 --> 01:05:00,230
Are you doing that on purpose?

980
01:05:00,314 --> 01:05:01,607
Are you being an edgelord?

981
01:05:20,709 --> 01:05:22,461
Let me put it away.

982
01:05:31,261 --> 01:05:32,304
I'm out of coins.

983
01:05:40,354 --> 01:05:41,521
Shall we go?

984
01:05:43,357 --> 01:05:44,608
Okay.

985
01:05:51,031 --> 01:05:52,199
Your bag.

986
01:06:48,296 --> 01:06:50,090
On the day I broke up with him,

987
01:06:50,674 --> 01:06:54,052
I kissed another man.

988
01:07:26,460 --> 01:07:28,211
TRUE TO LOVE

989
01:07:28,295 --> 01:07:31,423
-I heard about some mistake yesterday.
-She told you about it?

990
01:07:31,506 --> 01:07:33,508
-It's me.
-We both made a mistake yesterday.

991
01:07:33,592 --> 01:07:35,594
That's very misleading. Let's be careful.

992
01:07:35,677 --> 01:07:38,805
What are you doing? Stop! Oh, my!

993
01:07:38,889 --> 01:07:41,892
-...to avoid such a mistake again.
-Something urgent came up.

994
01:07:41,975 --> 01:07:42,976
-Do you like me?
-No.

995
01:07:43,059 --> 01:07:44,311
Me neither.

996
01:07:44,394 --> 01:07:47,522
-So sorry, Young-hoon came to Korea.
-Young-hoon!

997
01:07:47,606 --> 01:07:48,940
He insisted I come see him.

998
01:07:49,024 --> 01:07:51,276
Thanks, sorry, love you.

999
01:07:51,359 --> 01:07:53,528
-T-S-L.
-On a day like this...

1000
01:07:53,612 --> 01:07:55,864
I don't wanna drink by myself
on a day like today.

1001
01:07:55,947 --> 01:07:57,240
I don't feel like dating.

1002
01:07:57,324 --> 01:07:59,576
-Is today special?
-Can't spend today like this.

1003
01:07:59,659 --> 01:08:01,286
-Are we going out?
-Let's go.

1004
01:08:01,369 --> 01:08:04,706
Su-hyeok? Making a man like him fall
for me is child's play.

1005
01:08:04,790 --> 01:08:05,707
Need some fresh air.

1006
01:08:05,791 --> 01:08:07,250
A mistake again? I should let you off?

1007
01:08:07,334 --> 01:08:10,378
You don't care about others.
How can you be so selfish?

1008
01:08:10,462 --> 01:08:11,797
Let me apologize.
